cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about using deep neural networks for lesion segmentation in medical images, specifically for multiple sclerosis (MS) from multi-contrast MRI. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Neural networks are used, so neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) is also a possibility. Finally, medical imaging (cs.MM) is a possible category as well.
